<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Workshop Setup on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/workshop-setup/</link><description>Recent content in Workshop Setup on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/workshop-setup/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>1. Using SWiPE</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/workshop-setup/1-swipe/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/workshop-setup/1-swipe/</guid><description>&lt;h5 id="configure-your-org-using-swipe"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Configure your Org using SWiPE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#configure-your-org-using-swipe" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--info"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12" y2="12"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12.01" y2="8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Important Information&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SWiPE&lt;/strong&gt; does &lt;strong&gt;not&lt;/strong&gt; provision EC2 instances. These instances are provisioned separately using &lt;strong&gt;Splunk Show&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SWiPE&lt;/strong&gt; is an online tool designed to help you configure a workshop environment in Splunk Observability Cloud. You can access &lt;strong&gt;SWiPE&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://swipe.splunk.show" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;here&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:0.75em;opacity:0.6;"&gt;&amp;#x2197;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/swipe.png" alt="SWiPE" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SWiPE&lt;/strong&gt; will perform the following tasks your workshop environment:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>2. Using Splunk Show</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/workshop-setup/2-splunk-show/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/workshop-setup/2-splunk-show/</guid><description>&lt;h5 id="observability-workshop-templates"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Observability Workshop Templates&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#observability-workshop-templates" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Splunk Show offers two templates for Observability workshops. Select the one that best fits your needs:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
 &lt;thead&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Workshop Type&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Description&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Template&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/thead&gt;
 &lt;tbody&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Splunk4Rookies - Observability&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;This workshop template is designed for beginners. The template pre-deploys the &lt;strong&gt;OpenTelemetry Collector&lt;/strong&gt; and the &lt;strong&gt;Online Boutique&lt;/strong&gt; application. Attendees only need a browser to participate and complete the workshop.&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="https://show.splunk.com/template/262/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rookies&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:0.75em;opacity:0.6;"&gt;&amp;#x2197;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/rookies.png" alt="Rookies" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Splunk4Ninjas - Observability&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;This workshop template is tailored for &lt;strong&gt;advanced&lt;/strong&gt; users. The template sets up an instance with all necessary tools for hands-on activities. No resources are deployed or running at launch, allowing attendees to configure and deploy as needed.&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href="https://show.splunk.com/template/428/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ninja&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:0.75em;opacity:0.6;"&gt;&amp;#x2197;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/ninjas.png" alt="Ninjas" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--info"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ninja Workshops Only&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>3. Workshop Clean-up</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/workshop-setup/3-clean-up/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/workshop-setup/3-clean-up/</guid><description>&lt;h5 id="workshop-cleanup"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Workshop Cleanup&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#workshop-cleanup" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After completing your workshop session, it’s important to clean up the environment to save costs and ensure resources are properly managed. Use &lt;strong&gt;SWiPE&lt;/strong&gt; to handle the cleanup process efficiently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h5 id="what-swipe-deletes"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What SWiPE Deletes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#what-swipe-deletes" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SWiPE automates the following cleanup tasks:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Delete all users&lt;/strong&gt; associated with the workshop.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Delete the team&lt;/strong&gt; created for the workshop.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Delete tokens&lt;/strong&gt;, including INGEST, API, and RUM tokens.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Delete user dashboards&lt;/strong&gt; created during the workshop.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/delete-workshop.png" alt="Delete Workshop" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>4. Trial Org Configuration</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/workshop-setup/4-org-configuration/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/workshop-setup/4-org-configuration/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="log-observer-connect"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Log Observer Connect&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#log-observer-connect" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The workshops require a Log Observer Connect configuration to be setup. This is required to be able to send logs from the workshop instances to Splunk Cloud/Enterprise. &lt;strong&gt;SWiPE&lt;/strong&gt; provides a simple form to configure this and is available &lt;a href="https://swipe.splunk.show/log_observer_connect" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;here&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span aria-hidden="true" style="font-size:0.75em;opacity:0.6;"&gt;&amp;#x2197;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/log-observer-connect.png" alt="Log Observer Connect" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="log-field-aliasing"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Log Field Aliasing&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#log-field-aliasing" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Log Field Aliasing configuration is required to ensure Related Content works correctly in the Splunk Observability Cloud UI. Configure as per the following:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>5. Presenter Mode</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/workshop-setup/5-presenter-mode/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/workshop-setup/5-presenter-mode/</guid><description>&lt;h5 id="what-is-presenter-mode"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Presenter Mode?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#what-is-presenter-mode" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Presenter mode reveals delivery cues — timing hints, &amp;ldquo;kick this off in the background now&amp;rdquo; prompts, and other guidance for the person running the workshop — that are hidden from attendees by default. Notes are authored inline alongside the step they relate to, so you see them in context while presenting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h5 id="turning-presenter-mode-on"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Turning Presenter Mode On&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#turning-presenter-mode-on" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Append &lt;code&gt;?presenter=1&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;strong&gt;any&lt;/strong&gt; workshop URL and load the page once. For example:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>